pullRequest.body:
Added analogue of [LinearEquiv.ofInjective](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Basic.html#LinearEquiv.ofInjective) but for `ContinuousLinearEquiv` on Banach spaces.

Added analogue of [LinearMap.rangeRestrict](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Basic.html#LinearMap.rangeRestrict) but for `ContinuousLinearMap`.

Also I updated a docstring that had the old name of a theorem.

Throughout the library we have things like [ContinuousLinearMap.codRestrict](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/Basic.html#ContinuousLinearMap.codRestrict) which allow us to restrict a morphism to an appropriate codomain, and also versions specific to the range of the morphism (e.g., [LinearMap.rangeRestrict](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Basic.html#LinearMap.rangeRestrict)). However, `ContinuousLinearMap.rangeRestrict` seems to be missing.

1. Can you add `ContinuousLinearMap.rangeRestrict`?
2. Provide a lemma linking your new definition to it?

Thanks! Almost there. Please wait for CI after you make the edits before merging.

bors d+

Given the other existing things in the library, I think it makes sense to call this `ContinuousLinearMap.rangeEquiv`. Don't forget to rename the lemma too, and shuffle arguments to new lines for style so the spacing isn't weird.
```suggestion
noncomputable def rangeEquiv
```
Please write the LHS as a coercion instead of using `ContinuousLinearEquiv.toContinuousLinearMap`, unless we don't have that coercion, in such case, please ping me.
Turns out Lean4's intelligent coercion insertion works here without needing `.toContinuousLinearMap`!
Please use equality of functions here (unapplied) and call it `coe_rangeEquiv`

I've replaced this lemma with `(f.rangeEquiv hinj hclo : E â†’ LinearMap.range f) = f.rangeRestrict`, so that when `rangeEquiv` is applied as a function, `simp` can use all the lemmas for `ContinuousLinearMap.rangeRestrict`. I will wait for your confirmation before merging this one.
No, I think we want to go straight to `f`, but now that you mention it, we're missing the `simp` lemma `coe_rangeRestrict` as well, so please add that.

Going straight to `f` has the issue that `f` maps to `F` but `f.rangeEquiv _ _` maps to `LinearMap.range f`. Then the equality between functions will not work unless I insert a composition with inclusion. Or unless I misunderstood your suggestion.
I've added `coe_rangeRestrict`, but I'm not understanding your suggestion. Could you write the lemma statement of going straight to `f`?
Sorry, I was talking nonsense. Ignore me.

pullRequest.title: [Merged by Bors] - feat: injective continuous linear map with closed range is a continuous linear equivalence
